name: FI (10)
description:
This 2-vehicle crash occurred on a controlled-access roadway. This roadway is divided by a median, straight, downhill and dry. There are 2 westbound lanes with paved shoulders on both sides. The posted speed limit for this roadway is 113 kmph (70 mph). This crash occurred during daylight hours with no adverse atmospheric conditions.
vehicle1 (vehicle1), a vehicle1 pickup, was westbound in lane 1. vehicle2, a vehicle2, was parked on the right shoulder due to a previous crash. vehicle1 departed the roadway to the right and the front struck the left side of vehicle2. vehicle1 continued westbound and the front struck a guardrail off the right side of the roadway. the right front wheel of vehicle1 broke off and caused undercarriage damage to vehicle1. vehicle1 then reentered the roadway rotating counterclockwise, crossed both lanes and departed the roadway to the left. vehicle1 came to rest facing west in the median. both vehicles were towed due to damage.
